<html>
<head>
<title>Beta installation instructions - ForgedUI</title>
<meta name="layout" content="main" />
<style type="text/css" media="screen">
</style>
<script type="text/javascript">
var betaRegURL = "${createLink(action:'register',controller:'user')}";
var betaSurveyURL="${createLink(action:'completeSurvey',controller:'user')}";
</script>
</head>
<body>
	<!-- VISUAL SECTION -->
	<div id="visual_section">
		<div class="beta_instructions_left">
			<h3 class="color_strong">Beta installation Instructions</h3>
			
			<ol>
				<li>
					<h3>Uninstalling old beta and dependencies</h3>
					
					<ol class="dep_list">
						<li><p>
						Open and login to your "Titanium Studio", click the "Help" menu on top and click "Install New Software"						
						<img src="images/beta_installation_screenshots/Help_install_new_software.png" class="install_instructions_img" style="height: 278px; width: 612px;" />						 						
						</p></li>
						<li><p>						
						Click on the "What's already installed" link as shown below <br/>						
						<img src="images/beta_installation_screenshots/whats_already_installed.png" class="install_instructions_img" style="height: 535px; width: 628px;" />
						</p>
						</li>
						<li>
						<p>
						From the list that appears on your screen choose "ForgedUIEditor", "Graphical Editing Framework GEF", as well as "Graphical Editing Framework Draw2D" by using CTRL + Click on Windows, CMD+ Click on Mac, or using the Shift and Arrow keys.
						then click uninstall. <br/>
						<img src="images/beta_installation_screenshots/uninstall_all.png" class="install_instructions_img" style="height: 638px; width: 584px;" />
						</p>						
						</li>
						
						<li>
						<p>
						Confirm the uninstallation of the previous plugins by clicking Finish<br/>  
						<img src="images/beta_installation_screenshots/uninstall_confirm.png" class="install_instructions_img" style="height: 442px; width: 444px;" />						
						</p></li>
						
						<li><p>
						When un-installation is completed, a new Window appears asking you Whether you need to restart to apply changes, apply changes without restarting, or an option to defer changes and to do that later. 
						Choose "Restart Now"<br/>
						<img src="images/beta_installation_screenshots/restart_now_after.png" class="install_instructions_img" style="height: 136px; width: 440px;" />						
						</p></li>
						
						<li>
						<p>
						If you are unable to select all of the plugins mentioned in step 3 above at once , choose each one at a time, uninstall each one separately, following steps 1 to 5.
						</p></li>
																																								
					</ol>
					</li>
					
					
					<li>
					<h3>Installing ForgedUI</h3>
					
					<ol class="dep_list">
						<li><p>
						Open and login to your "Titanium Studio", click the "Help" menu on top and click "Install New Software"	a second time					
						<img src="images/beta_installation_screenshots/Help_install_new_software.png" class="install_instructions_img" style="height: 278px; width: 612px;" />						 						
						</p></li>
						<li><p>						
						A new window pops up asking you to either choose an available update site or add a new one. 
						Click the "Add" button then in the new Window Type "ForgedUI Beta 2 Updates" as the Repository name.
						<span style="font-weight: bold; font-size: 14px;">
						ForgedUI is currently in closed beta, therefore the repository location is not made public at this time. Users who are chosen for the beta will receive the correct URL to use   
						as the repository Location. 
						</span> 
						type in the correct location and then 
						Click OK <br/>
						
						<img src="images/beta_installation_screenshots/new_update_site_name.png" class="install_instructions_img" style="height: 161px; width: 406px;" />
						</p>
						</li>
						<li>
						<p>
						Select both "Dependencies" and "ForgedUI Editor" groups , or select the 3 individual plugins "ForgedUIEditor", "Graphical Editing Framework GEF", as well as "Graphical Editing Framework Draw2D" then click next. <br/> 
						<img src="images/beta_installation_screenshots/beta_2_install_select_all.png" class="install_instructions_img" style="height: 572px; width: 660px;" />
						</p>						
						</li>
																		
						<li><p>
						A new screen appears asking you to confirm installation details, simply click "Next" 
						<img src="images/beta_installation_screenshots/confirm_install_all.png" class="install_instructions_img" style="height: 573px; width:660px;" />						
						</p></li>
						
						<li><p>
						A new screen appears asking you to accept / reject licenses. Accept the license agrement and click "Finish" 
						<img src="images/beta_installation_screenshots/accept_forgedui_license.png" class="install_instructions_img" style="height: 381px; width: 631px;" />						
						</p></li>
						
						<li><p>
						Wait for the installation to complete. The progress window will close automatically when installation is completed.
						<img src="images/beta_installation_screenshots/Wait_For_Installation_To_complete.png" class="install_instructions_img" style="height: 205px; width: 450px;" />						
						</p></li>
						
						<li><p>
						When installation is completed, a new Window appears asking you Whether you need to restart to apply changes, apply changes without restarting, or an option to defer changes and to do that later. 
						Choose "Restart Now"<br/>
						<img src="images/beta_installation_screenshots/restart_now_after.png" class="install_instructions_img" style="height: 136px; width: 440px;" />						
						</p></li>
					
						<li>You are now ready to start using ForgedUI editor</li>					
					</ol>
					</li>
					
			</ol>

			
			<div id="visual_buttons"></div>
		</div>
		<div class="visual_right"></div>

	</div>
	<div class="clear"></div>

	<div class="delimiter">
		<hr>
	</div>

</body>
</html>
